{
  "stem": "5795.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Carry on.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I applied.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I preached.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were ready to accept me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1933. 1933-- '32-- '32-33.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then they said to me, we can't afford to give you a proper salary, but we'd like you.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because we would like you to become a member of the board of shechita so the-- the town itself will pay 1/2 your salary.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I said, I don't mind, as long as it's arranged properly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "By I won't take up a position in opposition to the board of shechita.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I took, not an oath, I gave a solemn promise to the [NON-ENGLISH] and the chief Rabbi that I will not oppose them, not open-- what you call a-- a board of shechita in opposition.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Oh, oh, oh, the board of shechita of the town didn't accept me-- not me-- they didn't accept the congregation's plan.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I tried somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Suddenly, two years later, I get a letter-- will I accept the job.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In my naivete, or whatever you like to call it, I took it for granted.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It took them two years to solve the problem.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So it didn't dawn on me I should ask any more questions.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "To my horror, and disgust, and embarrassment, and heartbreak, I said goodbye to St.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Annes, signed up, as it were, in Leeds.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The following week, the president [LAUGHS] said to me, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We haven't come to any conclusion with the board of shechita.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You'll have to start an opposition shechita.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I said oh, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I said, I've burnt my boats.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I'm engaged-- planning to get married-- didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Other members of the congregation were sympathetically inclined towards me, but-- then I-- I looked over the building.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "In the cellars, it were-- it was very large underground rooms.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
